{{rank|battle|bound|York|738|impossible|greatest|property|started}}

===Spellings===
*[[inpossible]] ''(obsolete)''

===Etymology===
From French ''[[#French|impossible]]'', from Latin ''[[impossibilis]]'', from ''[[in-]]'' ‘not’ + ''[[possibilis]]'' ‘possible’, from ''[[posse#Latin|posse]]'' ‘to be able’ + suffix ''[[-ibilis]]'' ‘-able’.

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/ɪmˈpɒsɪbəl/}}
*{{audio|en-us-impossible.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Adjective===
{{en-adj}}

# Not [[possible]], not able to be done
#:''Nothing is impossible, only impassible.'' --[[w:Lewis Carroll|Lewis Carroll]], ''Alice in Wonderland''
#{{colloquial}} Of a person, very difficult to deal with.
#:''You never listen to a word I say - you're impossible!''

